Submission of Papers

Papers are invited on any aspect of the use of
Geographical Information Systems (GIS) or computer
mapping for Coastal Zone applications.

ABSTRACTS ONLY (maximum 500 words) should be
sent in the first instance, to arrive in Cork by 1st July 1994.
Authors of papers selected for presentation will be
notified, and submission of full papers will be required by
1st November 1994.

Abstracts will be made available to delegates at the
Symposium; it is intended that full papers will be
published either as a proceedings volume, or else as a
special issue of an appropriate International academic
journal.

Supporting programme

The paper sessions will take place over two full days. In
additional, an optional pre-Symposium excursion to
places of interest in Cork Harbour will be arranged for the
Friday before the Symposium starts, and if there is
sufficient demand, a further full-day post-Symposium
excursion to the less developed coastlines of West Cork
will also be arranged (NB: These events will be at
additional cost to participants)

Getting to Cork

Cork Airport, on the outskirts of the city, has direct
connections with airports in Britain and continental
Europe, as well as with Dublin. Further international air
connections, particularly to North America, may be made
via Shannon airport (approx 100 km from Cork) or
Dublin.

There are direct ferry connections between Cork and
Swansea (Wales, UK) and Roscoff and Le Harvre
(France), as well as from France and Britain to the Irish
ferry terminal at Rosslaire. An express bus service
connects Rosslaire with Cork. Cork is also well-served by
train connections from Dublin and intermediate stations,
and by express bus from most towns in Ireland.

Accommodation

Arrangements for accommodation will be the
responsibility of individual participants. Cork City has a
very good range of accommodation possibilities, ranging
from international-standard hotels to lower-cost youth
hostels and familly-run guest houses. Most are within easy
walking distance of the University. A list of recommended
establishments  will be sent to registrants on request.

Registration Fees

A registration form, etc. will be sent out with the Second
Circular. Please use the accompanying form to register
your interest and/or to offer a paper.

